UPDATE manual_sections
SET content_en = $MD$
# Management Roles

## Management Overview

> **üí° Our Leadership**: At Alamo Prime, management is the foundation of operational excellence, team development, and guest satisfaction. Our leaders embody the S.H.O.W. framework while driving business success and creating exceptional work environments.

---

## Leadership Positions

### General Manager (GM)
**Primary Mission**: Overall restaurant leadership, strategic direction, and business performance

#### Core Responsibilities
- **Business Performance**: Revenue, cost control, and profitability management
- **Team Leadership**: Hiring, development, and performance management
- **Guest Experience**: Ensure exceptional service standards and guest satisfaction
- **Community Relations**: Represent Alamo Prime in the local community
- **Strategic Planning**: Long-term business planning and goal setting

#### Key Accountabilities
- **Financial Management**: Budget oversight, P&L responsibility, cost control
- **Team Development**: Create succession plans and career pathways
- **Brand Representation**: Uphold and enhance Alamo Prime reputation
- **Operational Excellence**: Ensure all departments meet standards
- **Regulatory Compliance**: Health, safety, and alcohol service compliance

### Assistant Manager
**Primary Mission**: Daily operations oversight and service excellence

#### Core Responsibilities
- **Daily Operations**: Coordinate front and back of house operations
- **Service Quality**: Monitor and maintain service standards
- **Team Supervision**: Direct supervision of hourly team members
- **Guest Relations**: Handle escalated guest issues and VIP guests
- **Inventory Management**: Oversee ordering, receiving, and inventory control

#### Key Accountabilities
- **Shift Leadership**: Manage opening and closing procedures
- **Quality Control**: Ensure food, beverage, and service quality
- **Problem Resolution**: Handle operational issues and guest complaints
- **Staff Development**: Train and develop hourly team members
- **Safety Compliance**: Ensure safe working conditions

### Bar Manager
**Primary Mission**: Beverage program excellence and bar operations

#### Core Responsibilities
- **Beverage Program**: Develop and maintain exceptional drink menu
- **Bar Operations**: Oversee bar staffing, training, and performance
- **Inventory Control**: Manage bar inventory, ordering, and cost control
- **Creative Development**: Create innovative cocktails and beverage offerings
- **Compliance**: Ensure responsible alcohol service and legal compliance

#### Key Accountabilities
- **Menu Development**: Design balanced, profitable beverage menu
- **Staff Training**: Train bartenders on techniques, recipes, and service
- **Cost Management**: Control pour costs and waste
- **Quality Assurance**: Maintain drink quality and presentation standards
- **Trend Awareness**: Stay current with beverage trends and innovations

---

## Daily Management Procedures

### Line Up / Team Update
**Objective**: Daily team alignment and communication

#### Meeting Standards
- **Daily gathering** of all staff before service
- **Discuss service points** and kitchen updates
- **Communicate menu changes** and wine list updates
- **Share pertinent restaurant news** and information
- **Set service goals** and expectations for the day

#### Meeting Content
- **Previous Service Review**: Highlights and improvement opportunities
- **Today's Focus**: Special events, VIP guests, large parties
- **Menu Updates**: 86'd items, specials, new offerings
- **Team Announcements**: Staff changes, promotions, recognitions
- **Service Standards**: Reinforce key standards and expectations

### Opening Management Responsibilities

#### Pre-Service Preparation
- **Team Readiness**: Ensure all team members present and properly uniformed
- **Station Inspection**: Verify all stations set to standards
- **Quality Checks**: Taste food, check bar setup, verify cleanliness
- **Briefing Coordination**: Lead pre-service team meetings
- **Final Inspection**: Dining room readiness and ambiance check

#### Operational Setup
- **System Verification**: POS systems, reservations, communication tools
- **Staff Assignments**: Confirm all positions properly staffed
- **Special Preparation**: Large parties, events, VIP accommodations
- **Safety Check**: Ensure all safety and security measures in place
- **Guest Communication**: Review reservations and special requests

### During Service Management

#### Service Oversight
- **Floor Presence**: Visible and available to team and guests
- **Quality Monitoring**: Observe service standards and food quality
- **Guest Interaction**: Greet VIP guests, handle special requests
- **Problem Resolution**: Address issues promptly and professionally
- **Team Support**: Assist and guide team members as needed

#### Performance Management
- **Service Standards**: Ensure all team members meet standards
- **Timing Coordination**: Monitor kitchen and service timing
- **Guest Satisfaction**: Proactively ensure guest satisfaction
- **Staff Performance**: Real-time coaching and guidance
- **Operational Flow**: Ensure smooth operations between departments

### Closing Management Responsibilities

#### End-of-Night Procedures
- **Team Check-Out**: Ensure all team members check out properly
- **Financial Reconciliation**: Close out registers, review daily reports
- **Security Procedures**: Secure restaurant, set alarms
- **Next Day Preparation**: Setup for following day's operations
- **Communication**: Document issues and communicate to next manager

#### Quality Assurance
- **Cleaning Standards**: Verify all cleaning completed to standards
- **Inventory Assessment**: Note any inventory issues or needs
- **Equipment Check**: Ensure all equipment properly shut down
- **Maintenance Issues**: Document and report any maintenance needs
- **Service Review**: Note service successes and improvement areas

---

## Leadership Excellence Standards

### Team Development

#### Staff Training and Development
- **Onboarding Programs**: Comprehensive new hire training
- **Cross-Training**: Develop multi-skilled team members
- **Skill Enhancement**: Ongoing training and skill development
- **Career Planning**: Create growth opportunities for team members
- **Performance Management**: Regular feedback and evaluation

#### Performance Standards
- **Clear Expectations**: Define and communicate performance standards
- **Regular Feedback**: Provide consistent, constructive feedback
- **Recognition Programs**: Acknowledge and reward excellent performance
- **Corrective Action**: Address performance issues promptly and fairly
- **Succession Planning**: Develop future leaders from within

### Guest Experience Management

#### Guest Relations Excellence
- **VIP Guest Management**: Personalized service for regular guests
- **Problem Resolution**: Handle guest complaints and issues
- **Service Recovery**: Turn negative experiences into positive ones
- **Feedback Collection**: Gather and act on guest feedback
- **Relationship Building**: Create lasting guest relationships

