UPDATE manual_sections
SET content_en = $MD$
# Line Cook Standards

## Position Overview

**Primary Responsibility**: Line Cooks at Alamo Prime are skilled culinary professionals who execute recipes with precision, operate specific stations efficiently, and ensure the highest quality food preparation while maintaining excellent timing and coordination with the service team.

### Core Mission
> **üí° Your Craft**: As an Alamo Prime Line Cook, you are responsible for executing recipes, performing general production, and operating a specific station with others or individually, while ensuring preparation and service is of the highest possible quality in a timely manner.

---

## Recipe Execution Standards

### Precision and Consistency
- **Execute recipes precisely** following established standards
- **Maintain portion control** and presentation standards
- **Ensure food quality** meets Alamo Prime specifications
- **Convert recipes accurately** for different batch sizes
- **Understand and implement** mise en place principles

### Quality Control
- **Taste and adjust** seasonings as needed
- **Monitor cooking times** and temperatures
- **Inspect food quality** before service
- **Maintain consistency** across all preparations
- **Follow food safety** standards at all times

---

## Station Operation Procedures

### Station Setup and Organization
- **Set up work station** with required tools, equipment, and supplies
- **Inspect cleanliness** and working condition of all tools and equipment
- **Check production schedule** and pars for the day
- **Establish priority items** for daily preparation
- **Inform management** of supplies that need requisition

### Station Maintenance
- **Maintain clean and organized** station throughout service
- **Monitor and maintain** cleanliness, sanitation, and organization
- **Properly label and date** all products for safekeeping
- **Utilize proper food handling** techniques following health standards
- **Ensure station readiness** for next service period

---

## Quality Control and Food Safety

### Food Safety Standards
- **Follow all health and safety regulations** without exception
- **Maintain proper food temperatures** for hot and cold items
- **Implement first-in, first-out** rotation philosophy
- **Properly store** all food items to prevent contamination
- **Monitor and maintain** personal hygiene standards

### Sanitation Procedures
- **Clean and sanitize** all work surfaces regularly
- **Follow proper cleaning** procedures for equipment
- **Maintain sanitary conditions** in assigned work areas
- **Report any sanitation concerns** to management immediately
- **Participate in regular** deep cleaning schedules

---

## Equipment Operation and Maintenance

### Equipment Identification and Usage
- **Identify and safely use** all kitchen equipment
- **Operate equipment** according to manufacturer guidelines
- **Perform basic maintenance** checks on equipment
- **Report equipment malfunctions** promptly
- **Follow proper shutdown** procedures for all equipment

### Tool Management
- **Maintain tools** in clean, working condition
- **Check condition and cleanliness** of blenders, shakers, and other tools
- **Verify temperature** of refrigeration units and glass wash machines
- **Properly store** tools and equipment after use
- **Report damaged or missing** tools to management

---

## Communication Protocols

### Team Communication
- **Communicate effectively** with management and co-workers
- **Coordinate with kitchen team** for smooth operations
- **Inform management** of any issues or needs
- **Participate in pre-shift** meetings and briefings
- **Provide updates** on station status and readiness

### Guest Communication
