- **Kitchen Operations**: Food preparation and safety procedures
- **Bar Operations**: Beverage service and inventory management
- **Support Operations**: Cleaning, maintenance, and administrative tasks

---

## Opening Procedures Overview

### Pre-Service Preparation Timeline

#### 2-3 Hours Before Opening
- **Management Arrival**: Leadership team arrives and begins setup
- **System Activation**: POS systems, lights, music, security systems
- **Kitchen Preparation**: Line setup, prep work, equipment checks
- **Bar Setup**: Stocking, preparation, equipment verification
- **Dining Room Setup**: Table setting, ambiance preparation

#### 1-2 Hours Before Opening
- **Team Arrival**: Hourly team members arrive and begin station setup
- **Station Preparation**: Individual station setup and organization
- **Quality Checks**: Food tasting, beverage verification, cleanliness checks
- **Briefing Preparation**: Management prepares for pre-service meeting
- **Final Inspection**: Complete restaurant readiness verification

#### 30-60 Minutes Before Opening
- **Pre-Service Meeting**: Team lineup and daily briefing
- **Final Touches**: Last-minute adjustments and preparations
- **Guest Communication**: Review reservations and special requests
- **Service Coordination**: Final coordination between departments
- **Door Opening**: Prepare to welcome first guests

### Key Opening Standards
- **Punctuality**: All team members arrive on time and ready
- **Completeness**: All setup tasks completed before opening
- **Quality Control**: All aspects meet Alamo Prime standards
- **Team Readiness**: All team members briefed and prepared
