# Opening Duties

## Opening Framework

> **üí° Our Foundation**: At Alamo Prime, successful opening procedures are the foundation of exceptional service. Our systematic approach ensures every team member is prepared, every station is ready, and every detail is attended to before we welcome our first guests.

---

## Opening Timeline

### 3 Hours Before Opening (Management Arrival)
**Objective**: Leadership team establishes foundation for service

#### Management Responsibilities
- **Arrival and Setup**: Management team arrives, activates systems
- **Building Security**: Disarm security systems, unlock facilities
- **System Activation**: POS systems, lights, music, temperature control
- **Initial Inspection**: Walk-through of entire facility
- **Supply Assessment**: Verify delivery arrivals and inventory levels

#### Leadership Preparation
- **Review Reservations**: Assess booking levels and special requests
- **Staffing Confirmation**: Verify all team members scheduled
- **Special Events**: Review any private parties or large groups
- **Daily Briefing Prep**: Prepare topics for pre-service meeting
- **Quality Standards Setup**: Establish quality control checkpoints

### 2 Hours Before Opening (Team Arrival)
**Objective**: Team members begin station preparation

#### Kitchen Team Arrival
- **Clock-In and Uniform**: Team arrives, changes into uniform, punches in
- **Team Verification**: Ensure all kitchen team members present and ready
- **System Setup**: Activate kitchen equipment and systems
- **Safety Check**: Verify all safety systems operational
- **Initial Briefing**: Kitchen team huddle and daily priorities

#### Front of House Team Arrival
- **Clock-In and Preparation**: FOH team arrives and prepares for service
- **Station Assignment**: Review station assignments and floor plan
- **Equipment Setup**: Prepare individual stations and tools
- **Uniform Check**: Ensure all team members in proper uniform
- **Mental Preparation**: Team members prepare for service mindset

### 90 Minutes Before Opening (Station Setup)
**Objective**: Individual station preparation and organization

#### Kitchen Opening Procedures
- **Print Daily Documents**: Opening/closing checklists, line checks, production sheets
- **Inventory Assessment**: Check walk-ins, low boys, and station supplies
- **Quality Verification**: Verify all products in house and properly rotated
- **Prep Organization**: Set up prep stations and organize mise en place
- **Safety Check**: Verify all equipment functioning properly

#### Front of House Setup
- **Host Stand Preparation**: Set up host station with all necessary supplies
- **Server Station Setup**: Prepare server stations with tools and supplies
- **Bar Setup**: Stock and organize bar for service
- **Dining Room Preparation**: Set tables, arrange ambiance elements
- **Restroom Check**: Ensure restrooms clean and stocked

### 60 Minutes Before Opening (Quality Control)
**Objective**: Final preparations and quality verification

#### Kitchen Quality Control
- **Line Check**: Complete line check for all stations
- **Food Quality**: Taste and verify food quality standards
- **Temperature Check**: Verify all holding temperatures
- **Presentation Standards**: Verify plating and garnish standards
- **Timing Coordination**: Coordinate kitchen timing with FOH needs

#### Front of House Quality Control
- **Table Setting Verification**: Ensure all tables set to standards
- **Ambiance Check**: Verify lighting, music, temperature
- **Supply Check**: Verify all supplies stocked and ready
- **Cleanliness Inspection**: Final cleanliness check of all areas
- **Service Readiness**: Verify all team members ready for service

### 30 Minutes Before Opening (Final Preparation)
**Objective**: Team briefing and final coordination

#### Pre-Service Meeting (Line Up)
- **Team Assembly**: All team members gather for daily briefing
- **Service Review**: Review previous service highlights and issues
- **Today's Focus**: Discuss reservations, VIPs, special events
- **Menu Updates**: Communicate 86'd items, specials, changes
- **Service Standards**: Reinforce key standards and expectations

#### Final Coordination
- **Station Final Check**: Final verification of all stations
- **Team Positioning**: Assign team members to opening positions
- **Guest Communication**: Review special requests and accommodations
- **Opening Countdown**: Prepare for door opening
- **Final Quality Check**: Last-minute quality verification

---

## Department-Specific Opening Procedures

### Kitchen Opening Duties

#### Executive Chef/Manager Responsibilities
- **Team Leadership**: Guide kitchen team through opening procedures
- **Quality Control**: Oversee all food quality and safety standards
- **Inventory Management**: Verify inventory levels and ordering needs
- **Coordination**: Coordinate with FOH for menu and timing
- **Problem Resolution**: Address any kitchen issues immediately

#### Line Cook Opening Procedures
- **Station Setup**: Prepare individual cooking stations
- **Mise En Place**: Organize and prepare all ingredients
- **Equipment Check**: Verify all cooking equipment operational
- **Quality Preparation**: Prepare components for service
- **Cleanliness**: Maintain station cleanliness throughout setup

#### Prep Cook Opening Procedures
- **Prep Station Setup**: Prepare prep areas and equipment
- **Ingredient Preparation**: Complete daily prep assignments
- **Inventory Organization**: Organize walk-ins and storage areas
- **Quality Control**: Verify ingredient quality and freshness
- **Cleaning**: Maintain prep area cleanliness

### Front of House Opening Duties

#### Host Opening Procedures
- **Host Stand Setup**: Prepare host station with all supplies
- **Reservation Review**: Review reservations and special requests
- **Menu Preparation**: Ensure menus clean and ready
- **Communication Setup**: Verify phone and reservation systems
- **Entrance Preparation**: Ensure entrance area clean and welcoming

#### Server Opening Procedures
- **Station Preparation**: Set up server stations with necessary supplies
- **Table Assignment**: Review station assignments and table numbers
- **Menu Knowledge**: Review menu updates and specials
- **Tools Preparation**: Prepare server tools and books
- **Team Coordination**: Coordinate with bus persons and other servers

#### Bus Person Opening Procedures
- **Station Setup**: Prepare bus station with supplies
- **Cleaning Supplies**: Organize cleaning and sanitizing supplies
- **Table Setup**: Assist with table setting and preparation
- **Team Coordination**: Coordinate with server team
- **Area Preparation**: Prepare assigned service areas

#### Bartender Opening Procedures
- **Bar Setup**: Stock and organize bar for service
- **Inventory Check**: Verify bar inventory and supplies
- **Equipment Preparation**: Prepare bar equipment and tools
- **Quality Preparation**: Prepare garnishes and mixers
- **Cleanliness**: Ensure bar area clean and organized

---

## Quality Control Standards

### Opening Quality Checkpoints

#### Kitchen Quality Standards
- **Food Quality**: All food items meet quality standards
- **Temperature Control**: All holding temperatures correct
- **Presentation Standards**: Plating and garnish standards met
- **Safety Standards**: All safety procedures followed
- **Cleanliness**: All areas clean and organized

#### Front of House Quality Standards
- **Table Settings**: All tables set to Alamo Prime standards
- **Ambiance**: Lighting, music, temperature appropriate
- **Cleanliness**: All areas clean and presentable
- **Supplies**: All necessary supplies stocked and ready
- **Team Readiness**: All team members prepared for service

#### Quality Verification Process
- **Manager Inspection**: Management conducts thorough inspection
- **Team Self-Check**: Team members verify own areas
- **Cross-Check**: Team members verify each other's areas
- **Final Approval**: Management gives final approval for opening
- **Documentation**: Opening checklist completed and signed

---

## Opening Documentation

### Daily Opening Checklist

#### Kitchen Opening Checklist
- [ ] All team members present and in uniform
- [ ] All equipment operational and safe
- [ ] All stations set up and organized
- [ ] All ingredients prepped and ready
- [ ] Quality control completed
- [ ] Safety procedures verified
- [ ] Cleaning standards met
- [ ] Coordination with FOH complete

#### Front of House Opening Checklist
- [ ] All team members present and in uniform
- [ ] Host station fully prepared
- [ ] All server stations ready
- [ ] Bar fully stocked and prepared
- [ ] Dining room set to standards
- [ ] Restrooms clean and stocked
- [ ] All systems operational
- [ ] Team briefed and ready

#### Management Opening Checklist
- [ ] Building security disarmed
- [ ] All systems activated
- [ ] Team verified and ready
- [ ] Quality inspections complete
- [ ] Reservations reviewed
- [ ] Special events coordinated
- [ ] Safety procedures verified
- [ ] Opening documentation complete

---

## Opening Communication Protocols

### Team Communication Standards

#### Pre-Service Meeting Content
- **Previous Service Review**: Highlights and improvement opportunities
- **Today's Focus**: Reservations, VIPs, special events
- **Menu Updates**: 86'd items, specials, new offerings
- **Staff Announcements**: New hires, promotions, recognitions
- **Service Standards**: Reinforcement of key standards

#### Communication Channels
- **Team Meetings**: Daily pre-service meetings
- **One-on-One Check-ins**: Individual team member check-ins
- **Department Coordination**: Inter-department communication
- **Management Updates**: Leadership communication to team
- **Issue Reporting**: Clear process for reporting issues

### Problem Resolution During Opening

#### Common Opening Issues
- **Staff Shortages**: Address staffing shortages immediately
- **Equipment Problems**: Address equipment issues promptly
- **Supply Issues**: Resolve supply problems before opening
- **Quality Concerns**: Address quality issues before service
- **Coordination Problems**: Resolve coordination issues between departments

#### Resolution Procedures
- **Immediate Assessment**: Quickly assess and understand issues
- **Team Communication**: Communicate issues to appropriate team members
- **Solution Implementation**: Implement solutions quickly
- **Documentation**: Document issues and resolutions
- **Follow-Up**: Verify solutions effective

---

## Opening Success Metrics

### Timing Standards
- **Management Arrival**: 3 hours before opening
- **Team Arrival**: 2 hours before opening
- **Station Setup**: 90 minutes before opening
- **Quality Control**: 60 minutes before opening
- **Final Preparation**: 30 minutes before opening
- **Door Opening**: Exactly on scheduled time

### Quality Standards
- **Team Readiness**: 100% of team members ready for service
- **Station Preparation**: All stations fully prepared
- **Quality Control**: All quality checks completed
- **Safety Standards**: All safety procedures verified
- **Guest Readiness**: Restaurant fully prepared for guests

---

## Continuous Improvement

### Opening Procedure Optimization

> **üöÄ Our Excellence**: #### Regular Review
- **Weekly Review**: Review opening procedure effectiveness
- **Team Feedback**: Gather team feedback on opening procedures
- **Performance Metrics**: Track opening performance metrics
- **Issue Analysis**: Analyze and address recurring issues
- **Process Improvement**: Continuously improve opening processes

#### Best Practices
- **Efficiency Optimization**: Improve opening efficiency
- **Quality Enhancement**: Enhance opening quality standards
- **Team Development**: Develop team opening skills
- **Technology Integration**: Utilize technology to improve opening
- **Standardization**: Standardize best practices across team

---

**At Alamo Prime, exceptional opening procedures create the foundation for flawless service and exceptional guest experiences. Every detail matters in preparing for success.** üö™

*Excellence begins before the first guest arrives - it starts with our commitment to perfect opening procedures.*
$MD$,
    word_count_en = 3500,
    updated_at = now()
